</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="93" type="activity">
<paragraph blockId="35.[123,1333,832,2279]" pageId="35" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[124,359,1889,1922]" pageId="35" pageNumber="93">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[371,510,1889,1922]" name="Sao Tome and Principe" pageId="35" pageNumber="93">Sao Tome</collectingCountry>
Collared Fruit Bats are presumably nocturnal. Individuals were always captured in mountain passes, probably during commuting flights.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
